name: JS Practice
body:
### Primitive Data Types
#### Numbers
```
const x = 5
```
#### Booleans
```
const x = true
```
#### Strings
```
const x = 'This is some text!'
```

### Basic Data Structures
#### Arrays
```
const x = []
```
```
const x = [1, 2, 3]
```
```
const x = ['array', 'of', 'strings']
```
```
const x = [{text: 'array'}, {text: 'of'}, {text: 'objects'}]
```
#### Objects
```
const x = {}
```
```
const x = {
  name: 'Curtis',
  age: 31,
  pets: ['winston', 'jasper', 'Pearl', 'Simon'],
  car: {
    make: 'Toyota',
    model: 'Scion iQ',
    year: 2012,
  }
}
```
#### Functions
```
const x = () => {}
```
```
const x = (a, b) => a + b

// OR

const x = (a, b) => {
  return a + b
}
```
